  "prompt": "Which is the best department T-Shirt design in IIT Madras?",
  "response": "Ah, the age-old IIT Madras T-Shirt competition! There's no single \"best\" design because it's *completely* subjective and often depends on the year. However, here's a breakdown of some departments that are consistently known for cool or interesting T-shirt designs, along with what makes them stand out:\n\n**Departments Often Mentioned for Good T-Shirt Designs (and why):**\n\n*   **Computer Science and Engineering (CSE):**\n    *   **Themes:**  In-jokes about coding, algorithms, data structures, puns, popular software, startup culture, and the overall tech world. They also do Meta designs.\n    *   **Why They're Popular:**  They often appeal to a broad range of students (even outside CSE) due to the relatability of tech humor.  They often incorporate visually appealing graphics and modern designs.\n    *   **Keep in Mind:**  Sometimes the humor can be a bit *too* inside-baseball if you're not familiar with the subject.\n\n*   **Electrical Engineering (EE):**\n    *   **Themes:** Circuit diagrams, waveforms, nods to famous electrical engineers, elements of electrical engineering, and general \"electricity\" puns.\n    *   **Why They're Popular:** Often clean and visually striking, incorporating recognizable electrical symbols and diagrams. Sometimes has a retro or vintage feel.\n\n*   **Mechanical Engineering (ME):**\n    *   **Themes:** Gears, tools, engines, vehicles, physics concepts, and witty sayings related to mechanics.\n    *   **Why They're Popular:**  Often bold and graphic, reflecting the more \"hands-on\" nature of the field.\n\n*   **Chemical Engineering (ChemE):**\n    *   **Themes:** Chemical structures, reactions, lab equipment, elements from the periodic table, and puns related to chemical processes.\n    *   **Why They're Popular:** Unique and creative use of chemical elements and structures.\n\n*   **Aerospace Engineering (AE):**\n    *   **Themes:** Airplanes, rockets, space, aerodynamics, and aviation history.\n    *   **Why They're Popular:**  Cool visuals related to flight and space.\n\n*   **Ocean Engineering (OE):**\n    *   **Themes:** Ships, marine life, waves, and engineering involved in ocean-based infrastructure.\n    *   **Why They're Popular:** Their designs are often very creative.\n\n**General Factors That Make a Good IIT Madras T-Shirt Design:**\n\n*   **Relevance:**  Clearly represents the department's identity.\n*   **Creativity:**  Original and clever concept.\n*   **Humor:**  Incorporates inside jokes or puns in a way that's broadly appealing.\n*   **Visual Appeal:**  Good use of color, typography, and graphics.\n*   **Wearability:**  A design that people will actually want to wear! (Not too cluttered or overly technical).\n*   **Quality of Printing:** This is a crucial point. A great design can be ruined by poor printing.\n\n**How to Find Examples (This is Key!):**\n\n*   **IIT Madras Alumni Groups (Facebook, LinkedIn):**  The *best* place to find examples! Search for keywords like \"IIT Madras T-Shirt,\" \"[Department Name] T-Shirt,\" etc. in these groups.  Alumni often share photos of old designs.\n*   **IIT Madras Student Social Media (Instagram, Facebook):**  Look for pages or accounts run by student clubs and organizations within each department.\n*   **Word of Mouth (If You Know Someone at IIT Madras):**  The most reliable method! Ask current students or recent graduates for their opinions and examples.\n\n**In summary, while I can't declare a single \"best,\" the CSE, EE, ME, and ChemE departments are consistently cited as having strong designs.  Your best bet is to do some digging on social media and alumni networks to see examples and form your own opinion!**\n",
